My first Mother’s Day is not just a celebration — it’s a reminder of strength, healing, and deep love.

The day after I gave birth to my baby boy, I was diagnosed with pancreatitis. I spent 21 days in the hospital, away from my newborn, in pain, physically weak, and emotionally broken.
Not being able to hold him, feed him, or even be near him — it shattered me.
But in that darkness, I had one shining light — my mother-in-law, whom I lovingly call Mom @rajeshwariatrey 🥹
She stepped in with all her heart and soul, caring for my baby like her own. Even today, as I recover, she continues to be my strength, helping raise him with so much love. I’ll forever be grateful.🧿🥹❤️

I couldn’t breastfeed due to my health and medications — the hardest decision of my life.
Every time I see him taking top feed, I silently cry. But I know this choice was necessary — for both of us.
I still hold onto hope that once I’m healthy, I’ll try again. That’s what mothers do — we never stop trying.

To every mom out there navigating unexpected journeys — you are enough.
And to my baby boy — I may not be doing everything, but I’m giving you all the love I have.

Happy Mother’s Day — to the women who carry love in their hearts and strength in their souls.

#MothersDay #NewMomJourney #MyBabyBoy #FirstMothersDay
